### ============================================================================
### Screenshot Capture Service — API Tests
### ============================================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@apiKey = dev-api-key


### ============================================================================
### Health & Monitoring
### ============================================================================

### Liveness probe
GET {{baseUrl}}/healthz

###

### Readiness probe (checks database)
GET {{baseUrl}}/readyz

###

### Prometheus metrics
GET {{baseUrl}}/metrics


### ============================================================================
### Captures
### ============================================================================

### Create a single capture job
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/captures
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

{
  "url": "https://github.com",
  "entity_type": "application",
  "entity_id": "github-home",
  "options": {
    "viewports": ["card", "detail"],
    "wait_strategy": "domcontentloaded",
    "delay_after_load_ms": 3000
  }
}

###

### Create a capture with callback URL
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/captures
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

{
  "url": "https://example.com",
  "entity_type": "template",
  "entity_id": "example-template",
  "callback_url": "https://your-server.com/webhook/capture-done",
  "options": {
    "viewports": ["card"],
    "wait_strategy": "networkidle",
    "wait_selector": "#main-content",
    "wait_timeout_ms": 20000,
    "delay_after_load_ms": 2000
  }
}

###

### Create a capture with default options
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/captures
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

{
  "url": "https://example.com",
  "entity_type": "deployment",
  "entity_id": "deploy-v1"
}

###

### Bulk capture (multiple URLs)
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/captures/bulk
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

{
  "items": [
    {
      "url": "https://github.com",
      "entity_type": "application",
      "entity_id": "github-page"
    },
    {
      "url": "https://example.com",
      "entity_type": "template",
      "entity_id": "example-page"
    },
    {
      "url": "https://httpbin.org/html",
      "entity_type": "template",
      "entity_id": "httpbin-html"
    }
  ],
  "priority": "high"
}

###

### Check job status (replace with actual job_id)
@jobId = 5c064d01-832f-4cd5-af70-a5d503cce4ba
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/captures/{{jobId}}
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}


### ============================================================================
### Entity Screenshots
### ============================================================================

### Get latest screenshots for an entity
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/entities/application/github-home/screenshots
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

###

### Get screenshots for a template
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/entities/template/example-template/screenshots
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

###

### Delete all screenshots for an entity
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/v1/entities/template/example-template/screenshots
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}


### ============================================================================
### Webhook Events
### ============================================================================

### Template published event (requires HMAC-SHA256 signature)
### Generate signature: echo -n '<body>' | openssl dgst -sha256 -hmac "your-webhook-secret"
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/events
Content-Type: application/json
X-Webhook-Signature: <replace-with-hmac-sha256-hex-signature>

{
  "event_type": "template.published",
  "entity_type": "template",
  "entity_id": "new-template-456",
  "url": "https://example.com/preview/new-template-456",
  "timestamp": "2025-01-15T10:30:00.000Z"
}

###

### Deployment finished event
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/events
Content-Type: application/json
X-Webhook-Signature: <replace-with-hmac-sha256-hex-signature>

{
  "event_type": "deployment.finished",
  "entity_type": "deployment",
  "entity_id": "deploy-789",
  "url": "https://my-app.example.com"
}
